The paper deals with subsampling stationary random processes on graphs, which is a topic that falls under the umbrella of signal processing on graphs. Therefore, cs.SI (Signal Processing) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves estimation of the power spectrum of the graph signal, which is a problem in information theory, making cs.IT (Information Theory) another likely sub-category. The use of least squares and greedy algorithms for subsampling and reconstruction suggests that the paper may also be relevant to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.SP (Speech Processing). Finally, the use of random processes and power spectra suggests that the paper may be relevant to cs.NA (Numerical Analysis).
